The alert showing `no application found to open this attachment` meant the attachment is downloaded but there isn't any app installed to open that file.
` Is the file supposed to overwrite another so file in the app's directory? `
>this attack has ability to overwrite arbitrary files but i am using a directory which doesn't have any native libs, you can see this  in apps logcat when apps tries to load library 
from `/data/data/com.evernote/lib-1/` everytime logcat shows `not found` in that directory. 

`How can we verify that the path traversal attack has placed the file where it was supposed to be placed?`
> yes we can verify the path transversal attack was successful by seeing app's logcat. 

### When there isn't any file in `/data/data/com.evernote/lib-1/` directory, before the attack
{F1490361}
 you can see it says `libjnigraphics.so not found on /data/user/0/com.evernote/lib-1` 

### When the path transversal attack gets succesful
{F1490370}
now you can see it says `SoLoader: libjnigraphics.so found on /data/user/0/com.evernote/lib-1`

